                     <interp inst="def2-1925-18470816" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1925-18470816" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1925-18470816" type="surname" value="WALKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1925-18470816" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHNWALKER</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18470816-1925-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1925-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1925-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> stealing 1 handkerchief, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 3 half-crowns; and 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the pro<lb></lb>perty of <persName id="t18470816-name-1068" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1068" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1068" type="surname" value="BURNELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1068" type="given" value="ARTHUR"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18470816-1925-offence-1 t18470816-name-1068"></join>Arthur Burnell</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1069" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1069" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1069" type="surname" value="BURNELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1069" type="given" value="ARTHUR"></interp>ARTHUR BURNELL.</persName>
                  </hi> I live in James'-terrace, Camden-town—on the evening of the 23rd of July, I was with some friends in the Commercial-road—I got intoxicated—I then came to Whitechapel-raod—I lost a silk handkerchief, and about 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in money—some was in pocket behind, and some in my trowsers pocket—this is my handkerchief, when I got sober I identified it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1070" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1070" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1070" type="surname" value="KELLY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1070" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS KELLY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi> 119 <hi rend="italic">H.</hi>) I was in plain clothes in White-chapel-road that night, and saw the prisoners with Burnell—they brought him to the Brass Founder's Arms—he would not go in there, and they took him to Fieldgate-street, and then on to the Commercial-road—they got him into a public-house—he was there perhaps twenty minutes—they went from there to a cook's shop—I saw Burnell use his handkerchief before he went into the cook's shop—I staid till they came out—they went to another public-house, and were still dragging him along—they then separated—I took Walker on suspicion of robbing Burnell—on our way across the road, Walker tried to drop this handkerchief, but we caught it—Kirkman was standing a little further on.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Kirkman had left the prose<lb></lb>cutor? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—Walker used a great deal of exertion to get the prosecutor</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184708160189"></xptr>
               <p>into the public-house—I have inquired about Kirkman, and find he is a respectable hard-working man.</p>
